{
  "id": "019d2e8e-60a4-7cc0-b9de-2884dbb5ca07",
  "content": "# Tiered Knowledge Schema Foundation — Implementation Record (2026-03-27)\n\n## What Was Implemented (Issue #14, PR #29)\n\nSchema foundation for tiered knowledge lifecycle management, merged to master.\n\n### Types Added (corvia-common/src/types.rs)\n- `MemoryType` enum: Structural, Decisional, Episodic (default), Analytical, Procedural\n  - Derives: Debug, Clone, Copy, Default, PartialEq, Eq, Hash, Serialize, Deserialize\n  - Has Display, FromStr, serde rename_all=snake_case\n- `Tier` enum: Hot (default), Warm, Cold, Forgotten\n  - Same derives plus PartialOrd, Ord (natural ordering: Hot > Warm > Cold > Forgotten)\n  - Variant order in enum is reversed (Forgotten first) to get correct Ord derivation\n- `PinInfo` struct: { by: String, at: DateTime<Utc> }\n  - Replaces 3 separate pin fields — makes invalid states unrepresentable\n\n### KnowledgeEntry Fields Added\nmemory_type, confidence (Option<f32>, clamped 0-1), last_accessed, access_count (u32, saturating), tier, tier_changed_at, retention_score (Option<f32>), pin (Option<PinInfo>). All #[serde(default)].\n\n### Key API Methods\n- `MemoryType::from_content_role(Option<&str>)` — auto-classification via match\n- `MemoryType::is_known_content_role(&str)` — delegates to try_from_role\n- `with_confidence(f32)` — clamps to [0,1], rejects NaN\n- `record_access()` — saturating_add + timestamp\n- `pin(by)` / `unpin()` / `is_pinned()` — safe pinning API\n\n### Design Decisions Made During Review\n1. PinInfo struct over 3 separate fields (SWE + API + Rust reviewers agreed)\n2. Tier has PartialOrd/Ord with reversed variant order for natural ordering\n3. classify_memory_type uses match (not linear scan array) with shared try_from_role\n4. tracing dependency added to corvia-common for unmapped content_role warnings\n5. Free functions kept as thin wrappers over associated methods for backward compat",
  "source_version": "mcp",
